<h5>On this page and in various sections of the website, www.olympiadfoundation.in (&#8220;Olympiad Foundation website&#8221; or “the website”), are set out the terms and conditions (“Terms”) on which you may access and make use of our website. These Terms constitute a binding legal agreement between you as user (whether or not you are a Registered User, as defined below) and Olympiad Foundation Ltd,(“Olympiad Foundation” or “us”).</h5>
<p><strong>Please read these Terms carefully before you start to use the Olympiad Foundation website. By using the Olympiad Foundation website, you indicate that you accept these Terms and that you agree to abide by them. If you do not agree to these Terms, please refrain from using the Olympiad Foundation website. You warrant that you have the right, authority and capacity to enter into and be bound by these Terms and that by using the Olympiad Foundation website you will not be violating any law or regulation of the country in which you are resident. You are solely responsible for your compliance with all applicable local laws and regulations.</strong></p>
<p><strong>TERMS OF BUSINESS WITH SCHOOLS</strong></p>
<p>In addition to the Terms set out elsewhere on our website, a Client school (via its authorised representative) shall agree to be bound to the following terms of business:</p>
<p><strong>1. </strong><strong>Definitions</strong></p>
<p>In these Terms of Business:</p>
<p>‘Olympiad Foundation’ means Olympiad Foundation Limited.</p>
<p>‘Candidate’ means a person introduced by Olympiad Foundation to the client for the purpose of a permanent, fixed term position or temporary position with the client. This includes teachers a client has connected with via &#8216;Olympiad Foundation Explorer&#8217;.</p>
<p>‘Client’ means the person or organisation within an international school to whom a candidate is introduced. This includes the school itself.</p>
<p>‘Introduce’ means the provision by Olympiad Foundation to the Client of any details, whether written, oral or via the website, of a Candidate.</p>
<p>‘Regulations’ means the Conduct of Employment Agencies and Employment Business Regulations 2003 (as amended from time to time).</p>
<p>‘Terms of Business’ means these Employment Agency Terms of Business, any documents agreed or issued pursuant to the terms herein and any agreed variations.</p>
<p>Reference to the singular includes the plural and reference to the masculine includes any gender and vice versa.</p>
<p><strong>2. </strong><strong>General  </strong></p>
<p>A Candidate is introduced to the Client when Olympiad Foundation supplies, orally, in writing, or via its online platform, any information about the Candidate. A Candidate shall be deemed to have been introduced to the Client unless, within 72 hours (excluding weekends and bank holidays) of delivery to the Client of sufficient information to enable it to identify the Candidate, the Client notifies Olympiad Foundation in good faith that the Candidate is already in contact with the Client about an appointment.</p>
<p><strong>3. </strong><strong>Agreement of Terms of Business</strong></p>
<p>These Terms of Business shall be deemed to have been accepted and agreed by the Client from the time of using any of Olympiad Foundation’ services.</p>
<p><strong>4. </strong><strong>Our Fees</strong></p>
<p>4.1 Fees for Olympiad Foundation  service are charged if Olympiad Foundation is notified within ten days of the contract being signed. If a client fails to notify Olympiad Foundation within ten days, Olympiad Foundation will invoice the client the full fee for our Global service. <strong>See 8 below for the T&amp;Cs for Olympiad Foundation  service.</strong></p>
<p>4.2 Fees for Olympiad Foundation Global service will be charged at the rate agreed with the school. Fees for teachers, middle managers (eg Head of Department) and senior leaders will range depending on the role, the school&#8217;s location and the service required. For more information, email info@olympiadfoundation.in </p>
<p>4.3 Membership of Olympiad Foundation is free and entitles Clients to a school profile page and unlimited &#8216;Basic&#8217; adverts on Olympiad Foundation.</p>
<p>4.4 Olympiad Foundation may alter the fee levels from time to time and, if appropriate, the Client will be advised in writing.</p>
<p><strong>5. Paying the Introductory Fee</strong></p>
<p>5.1 The Client using Olympiad Foundation Global service must notify Olympiad Foundation within 72 hours if they appoint a Candidate whom Olympiad Foundation has introduced.  The Clients using our service must notify Olympiad Foundation within ten working days if they appoint a candidate they found via Olympiad Foundation. We define an appointment to be when there is a written agreement that the Candidate will accept the position, at which point the client will be invoiced.  The Client must pay the agreed fee within 30 days of the date on the invoice. If the Client fails to pay within this agreed period, then Olympiad Foundation shall be entitled to charge interest on any accounts which remain outstanding at the rate of 3% per calendar month or part thereof until the account is settled.</p>
<p>5.2 If a Client fails to pay an agreed introduction fee within 30 days, then Olympiad Foundation reserves the right to cancel the introduction fee and reissue the invoice for the full Global fee listed in our latest brochure. A reminder will be sent when the invoice is overdue.  If the invoice is still not paid within 7 days and a discount is applied, then a new invoice will be issued with the full fee as described in section 4.</p>
<p><strong>6. References</strong></p>
<p>6.1 The Client is responsible for reviewing, checking, and confirming any references (including the confirmation of any professional / academic qualifications and necessary background / safeguarding checks) and shall satisfy itself as to the suitability of any candidates prior to the engagement of a candidate by the Client.</p>
<p>6.2 The Client is responsible for obtaining work permits and/or such other permission to work as may be required, for the arrangement of medical examinations and/or any investigations into the medical history of the Candidate and satisfying any medical or other requirements, qualifications, or permission required by law applicable to the appointment.</p>
<p>6.3 Olympiad Foundation shall endeavour to ensure the suitability of any applicant introduced to the Client and to maintain a high standard of service and integrity, but Olympiad Foundation makes no warranty, express or implied, as to the suitability of any applicant introduced to the Client.</p>
<p>6.4 Olympiad Foundation shall not be liable to the Client for any loss, liability, damage, costs, claims or expenses suffered or incurred by the Client arising from, or connected with, the recruitment or engagement of any candidate by the Client, howsoever arising.</p>
<p>6.5 Candidates cannot access the references provided by current or former employers via their profiles.</p>
<p><strong>7. Rebates</strong></p>
<p>7.1 In the event a Candidate is hired via Olympiad Foundation Global service and does not commence employment or leaves the Client’s employment within 12 weeks of the commencement of employment (for any reason other than redundancy), the Client must notify Olympiad Foundation in writing within one week of the Candidate&#8217;s departure. The Client will then be entitled to a refund of 50% of the recruitment introduction fee.</p>
<p>7.2 For the avoidance of doubt, where the appointment is terminated with no notice, then the relevant period described in clause 7 ends on the date the appointment comes to an end and not (if different) the date when notice is given.</p>
<p>7.3 No refund will be made unless a) the recruitment introduction fee and all other fees and expenses have been paid in accordance with Clause 5; b) written notice is received by Olympiad Foundation within 7 working days of the termination of the candidate&#8217;s engagement; c) the termination in not due to redundancy and d) the Client undertakes not to re-engage the candidate within 12 months of the date of the termination.</p>
<p><strong>8. Olympiad Foundation service</strong></p>
<p>8.1 If a Client clicks on a candidate profile and then interviews and employs the candidate, it counts as an  hire and the Client will be invoiced for that hire. The Client recognises that Olympiad Foundation records every time a Client clicks on a candidate profile and can use this as evidence that the candidate was introduced by Olympiad Foundation.</p>
<p>8.2 If the Client hires a Candidate they have clicked on via our service, the Client must inform Olympiad Foundation within ten days of the candidate agreeing to the offer in writing. If the Client fails to inform Olympiad Foundation within ten days as outlined above, the introductory offer for teachers (for middle leaders and SLT) will no longer apply and Olympiad Foundation will invoice the Client for the full Global hire fee.</p>
<p>8.3 A Client may use both our service and Global services simultaneously. If a Client views, and then contacts a candidate via our service and Olympiad Foundation has already introduced that candidate via our Global service, then the Client will have to pay the agreed Global service fee. If a Client hires a candidate they found via and can provide evidence of contacting the candidate via service and subsequently Olympiad Foundation sends the same candidate to the Client (as a Global candidate), the Client will only pay the service fee as the Client first contacted the Candidate via the system.</p>
<p>8.4 The Client is responsible for its access and information on Olympiad Foundation and agrees never to share its login details with anyone outside the Client’s HR team. If a member of the Client’s HR team leaves the organisation, it is the Client’s responsibility to inform Olympiad Foundation and update the organisation’s login details.</p>
<p>8.5 Olympiad Foundation provides the platform, documentation and references on candidates profiles and does a basic candidate review. However, we expect the Client to be responsible for final background and safeguarding checks according to the Client’s internal policies and to comply with the legal requirement of the Client’s host nation.</p>
<p>8.6 The Client is responsible for the candidates it recruits via Olympiad Foundation . If a candidate is hired via service and the Candidate reneges on the contract with a Client (or leaves employment early), Olympiad Foundation will not provide a refund or offer an alternative Candidate free of charge.</p>
<p>8.7 The Client must keep Olympiad Foundation informed on all progress with candidates and copy <a href="mailto:info@olympiadfoundation.in">info@olympiadfoundation.in</a> on all emails to Olympiad Foundation candidates. Olympiad Foundation reserve the right to cancel the Client’s access to service at any point should they believe the Client is not acting in good faith.</p>
<p>8.8 The Client must never contact a candidate’s referee until the Client has interviewed a candidate (via Zoom or face-to-face) and the candidate (or Olympiad Foundation) has granted permission for his/her referees to be contacted.</p>
<p>8.9 The Client should not send a candidate more than two emails. If a candidate does not respond, the Client should refrain from contacting the candidate again. Clients can contact as many candidates as they wish but we recommend not contacting more than ten candidates for each vacancy per day. If a Client fails to comply with any of our expectations, Olympiad Foundation reserves the right to remove the Client’s access to candidates via our service.</p>
<p><strong>9. </strong><strong>Introductions</strong></p>
<p>9.1 The introduction of a Candidate to a Client by Olympiad Foundation is confidential. The Client must not, directly or indirectly, transfer or introduce a Olympiad Foundation Candidate to any other person, school, firm or company where they are subsequently appointed in a permanent or temporary position within one year of the date of the recruitment introduction of the Candidate to the Client by Olympiad Foundation. If this happens, the Client will have to pay Olympiad Foundation the full recruitment introduction fee,  as if the Client itself had appointed the Candidate.</p>
<p>9.2 When a Candidate is introduced to a Client via the Global service they will receive a &#8216;candidate recommendation&#8217; that includes confidential information about the Candidate. The Client should under no circumstances share this information with the Candidate. Should the Candidate directly or indirectly see the recommendation or its contents, the Client will be held responsible for any losses or damages.</p>
<p>9.3 If a Client agrees to use Olympiad Foundation Global service, the Client agrees to keep Olympiad Foundation copied into all emails to candidates. The Client should first copy in the Olympiad Foundation contact who first introduced the candidate or, in cases this is not possible, the Client should copy in <a href="mailto:info@olympiadfoundation.in">info@olympiadfoundation.in</a></p>
<p>9.4 If a Client agrees to use Olympiad Foundation Global service, the Client agrees to inform Olympiad Foundation of any updates to the status of the Client&#8217;s vacancies and must inform Olympiad Foundation within a week if a vacancy is filled (even if it is not a Olympiad Foundation candidate that has filled the vacancy).</p>
<p>9.5 If Olympiad Foundation introduces a candidate to a Client, the Client should inform Olympiad Foundation of whether or not it intends to interview the candidate within a week of the candidate being put forward. This may be done by replying to the initial email from Olympiad Foundation or by copying Olympiad Foundation in on an email sent directly to the candidate.</p>
<p><b>10. </b><strong>Data protection</strong></p>
<p>The Client and Olympiad Foundation will use and process personal data for recruitment purposes only and in accordance with EU General Data Protection Regulations.</p>

<p><b>11. Modifications to Terms and Conditions</b></p>
<p>Olympiad Foundation can vary these Terms of Business written under LAWS UNDER INDIA, Law by informing clients of changes.</p>
